<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-5078] Handle named pipe clients quickly disconnecting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5078</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the TPipeServer transport, if a client connects but disconnects before the acceptImpl method is able to create a TPipe instance the resulting exception causing the entire transport to stop.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can cause this issue using the SysInternals accesschk utility (&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/downloads/accesschk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/downloads/accesschk&lt;/a&gt;) to query the permissions of the named pipe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This has also been reported in osquery &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/osquery/osquery/issues/4280&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;osquery/osquery#4280&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
